# Committed hostname denylist — SHA-256 of each denied machine hostname, lowercased (#865).
#
# Why hashes, not plaintext: the gitignored config/identifiers.local.txt is absent in CI, so
# CI couldn't enforce hostnames — the blind spot that let a real machine name reach ~7 evidence
# docs (#861/#862/#864). A SHA-256 is safe to commit (it doesn't reveal the plaintext), so
# committing the digests lets CI catch a denied hostname without the hostname ever entering the
# tree. A hostname match reports its location only, never the token.
#
# SEED at go-public (operator): `just identifier-guard --deny-host <hostname>` appends the
# lowercased hash here. Deny only genuinely-sensitive machine names — NOT names that are
# legitimately public in the docs (e.g. a documented CI fleet). One hex digest per line;
# `#` comments allowed. Empty today: the hostname class is inert until seeded.
